For his new documentary on the rise and fall of disgraced theatre impresario Garth Drabinsky, director Barry Avrich went to visit his famous subject in prison – but he left his camera behind.“I went to see him at Beaver Creek a few times,” Avrich says, referring to the minimum-security institution near Gravenhurst, Ont., where Drabinsky is serving a five-year term for fraud and forgery.
